article.headline: Weber State 60, IPFW 47
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Lance Allred scored 14 points and pulled down 16 rebounds to lead Weber State to a 60-47 victory over Indiana-Purdue at Fort Wayne on Tuesday. Troy Goodell and Coric Riggs also each scored 14 for the Wildcats (8-11). The victory was the 100th win at Weber for coach Joe Cravens. David Simon scored 17 points to lead the Mastodons (4-16), who lost their third in a row. The Wildcats took an 18-9 lead, but the Mastodons responded with a 16-6 run and ended the first half with a 25-24 lead. Weber State recaptured the lead and cruised to the win in the second half on the 3-point shooting of Goodell and Brett Cox, who combined to hit 4-of-8 from behind the arc.
